      <section eId="sec_CHC-1410">
        <num>CHC 1410</num>
        <heading>1410. Â Violation of rights; reports; reports of abuse or neglect</heading>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1410__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>Alleged violations of the rights established by Article 1409 shall be reported immediately to the superintendent and there shall be a written record that:</p>
          </content>
          <paragraph eId="CHC-1410__subsec_A__subsec_1">
            <num>(1)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Each alleged violation has been thoroughly investigated and findings stated.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CHC-1410__subsec_A__subsec_2">
            <num>(2)</num>
            <content>
              <p>The results of such investigation were reported to the superintendent within twenty-four hours of the report of the incident.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1410__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>Abuse or neglect of any child shall be reported to a child protection agency in accordance with Chapter 5 of Title VI.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=72906</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
